      { q: "What is the difference between congruent and similar shapes?", a: "Congruent shapes are identical in size and shape — they have the same dimensions and angles. One can be placed exactly on top of the other. Similar shapes have the same shape (same angles) but different sizes — their corresponding sides are in the same ratio (proportion). All congruent shapes are similar, but not all similar shapes are congruent." }
